article.headline: Marshall 81, UCF 75
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- Hassan Whiteside had a triple-double -- 14 points, 14 rebounds and 10 blocked shots -- and Chris Lutz scored 21 points as Marshall overcame a 12-point second-half deficit to defeat Central Florida 81-75 on Wednesday night. The victory was the fifth straight for Marshall (14-2, 3-0 Conference USA), which led 76-65 before an 8-0 Knights' run cut the deficit to 76-73 on a three-point play by Marcus Jordan with 38 seconds left. The Thundering Herd then hit 5 of 6 free throws. Whiteside, who leads the nation in blocked shots, has the only triple-doubles in Marshall history. He had the other against Brescia University in December. A 12-2 Thundering Herd run early in the second half erased a 10-point UCF lead. Three straight three-pointers by Lutz gave Marshall a 66-59 lead with 6:29 remaining. Jordan, Michael Jordan's son, led UCF (9-7, 1-1) with a career-high 19 points.
